node.text:
This week we are thrilled to be celebrating the 15th anniversary of ferm LIVING. What initially began as just our founder, Trine Andersen, a bold idea and ten wallpaper designs, has since grown into an established design brand that fuses a Scandinavian mindset with global skills and traditions. 

As ferm LIVING has grown over the years, one thing remains the same: our ambition to inspire people to create a home where they can be comfortably and authentically themselves – a home that embraces you just as you are.

node.text:
This year, Christmas may very well be a smaller, more intimate affair than usual. So now is the perfect opportunity to unleash your creative side with a beautiful, thoughtful table setting that will make your cherished guests feel extra welcome and appreciated while setting the tone for cosy holiday celebrations.

To see more, follow the link in our bio.

node.text: Learn how to make your very own Poppykalas Advent wreath together with Thilde, the founder and creative mind behind @Poppykalas, a Floral Design Studio based in Copenhagen. Her distinctive, pastel-hued creations often take untamed and unexpected forms, at once both delicate and extravagant. In this tutorial, she shares a step by step guide as to how you can create a fun and unique Advent decoration with the use of dried flowers and the Bowl Candle Holder from ferm LIVING.

node.title: Poppykalas: How to Make Your Own Advent Wreath

node.text: A talk between Trine Andersen, Founder and Creative Director of ferm LIVING, and Julie @vonsperling, a hospitality expert with 20 years of experience from the world's leading hotels. Held during 3daysofdesign at the Home of ferm LIVING in Copenhagen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 08, 2021.

node.text:
The kids' room should be a sanctuary from the restrictions and boundaries of the outside world, allowing for both fiercely fun pillow fights and serene drawing sessions. Fill our lovely cotton Tent with Ladybird Embroidery with soft textiles and cuddly teddies to create a cosy hideaway in the kids' room where your little ones can play, read or relax.
​
​Visit our other account @fermlivingkids to view more inspiring content on how to transform the kids' room into a cosy sanctuary for your little one.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 07, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: The bathroom is a room that fulfils many different functions. Our Dora Clothes Stand presents a minimal, multifunctional solution with a hint of Japanese design aesthetics. Use it as a stylish drying rack which can neatly be folded and stored away when not in use, or as a minimalistic room divider that allows you to display your favourite garments.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 06, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Creating a tranquil atmosphere in your bedroom will allow for better rest, preparing you to take on the excitements and challenges of the day to come. With a simple and elegant design that is elevated just above the ground, our Japanese-inspired Kona series embraces the art of 'low living'. Let the Kona Side Table peek out from under the Kona Bed to provide a practical platform for a book, a cosy lamp or a cold glass of water.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 05, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: In the summer months, colourful flowers, lush green plants or even edible herbs, fruits and vegetables can transform your outdoor space into a green sanctuary. Give your green space a vibrant and classic look by creating a suspended garden with our Bau Balcony Boxes, which borrow their expression from the uncluttered lines and industrial surfaces of the Bauhaus architecture.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 04, 2021. May be an image of flower and indoor.

node.text: Creating a warm, inviting space requires careful attention to details. With an irregular, feminine form, our artfully oversized Verso Floor Vase recalls classic shapes from traditional pottery. Made entirely from stoneware with a reactive, high-gloss glaze that has been applied by hand, each individual vase is unique, and will help to add an unexpected, whimsical touch to your space.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 03, 2021. May be an image of sofa and living room.

node.text: Add an artistic, intriguing touch to your home with our Post Coffee Tables. Inspired by brutalism, the decorative tables play with volumes and feature intricate, alluring details that are complimented by three robust, cylindrical legs and a unique oak veneer panelling. Let the Post Coffee Table stand alone, or combine the two different sizes to create a cohesive living room landscape in two levels.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 02, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: While messy surroundings can be stressful, a tidy one will help bring you peace and calm. Made from raw, 100% recycled and biodegradable paper pulp, our lidded Paper Pulp Paper Bin gives you a handy, lightweight and stackable storage solution.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 01, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Your home should be a safe, secure space where you can be the most authentic, true version of yourself. Let the ambient light of our slim and elegant Arum Tall Wall Lamp illuminate the cosiest corner of your space, allowing you to curl up with a good book and a blanket in the sanctuary you call home.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on July 31, 2021. May be an image of furniture.

node.text: Summer calls for spending solitary afternoons letting the sun nourish your soul while you relish in a good book. With a quilted design padded for comfort and a functional shoulder strap for easy transportation, our True Quilted Rolling Mat is ideal for outdoor summer relaxation.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ferm LIVING on July 30, 2021 tagging @chelseagarmsy. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Nothing beats the feeling of spending a warm summer day enjoying the cooling ocean breeze at the beach. Make yourself some refreshing lemonade and serve it in our mouth-blown, sophisticated and contemporary Ripple Glasses and Carafe for the perfect beach drink. 
​
​Thank you to @chelseagarmsy for making us crave a beach day with this beautiful photo.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on July 29, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Your office should be a space for deep reflection as well as creativity and inspiration. Defined by its sturdy simplicity and classic combination of wood and brass, our Sector Desk can be combined with our Sector Shelves, allowing you to transform the wall of your office into one sleek, organised and cohesive workspace.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on July 28, 2021.

node.text: During the summer months, your outdoor space can be transformed into a truly special place with space to unwind, unplug and enjoy the moment. Behind the backrest of our sustainable, FSC™-certified Peka Bench, you’ll find a narrow shelf, making it the perfect spot to enjoy a cup of coffee or a glass of cold lemonade in the summer sun.
